<https://w3id.org/EVI#EvidenceGraph> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An EvidenceGraph is a directed acyclic graph\n\nEv = (Rn, r+, r-)\n\nwhere Rn is a set of Representations, r+ ∈ RnXRn is a set of supports relations, r- ∈ RnXRn is a set of challenge relations, and R+∩R- = Φ.\n\nEvidenceGraphs are bipolar argumentation frameworks (Cayrol &amp; Lagasquie-Schiex, 2009) represented as RDF named graphs." .
