<https://w3id.org/EVI#Article> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An Article is a (typically compound) textual document conveying a set of Claims and other DigitalObjects. Among these, an Article in EVI always conveys an assertion of its authorship in the form of a bibliographic self-reference." .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#packages> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#packages> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Instances of software can be packaged by the instances of containers." .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#directlySupportedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The use of directlySupportedBy property is intended to establish a direct relation between instances of DigitalObjects." .
