<https://w3id.org/EVI#MLModel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An MLModel is a computational model that has been trained on data to perform a specific task. It is a digital object that captures the learned parameters and architecture resulting from a machine learning training process (Computation)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#directlySupportedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "directlySupportedBy" .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#usedService> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The property usedService is a subproperty of used where domain is Computation and range is Service." .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#Annotation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Annotation is a Document that comments on or provides interpretibility of an analysis. The analysis could be based on an LLM analysis (or any analysis) of a Computation." .
