<https://w3id.org/EVI#describes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The describes property is used when a Method, generally composed with a block of text, narrates a prov:Activity that takes place." .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#sampleUsedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Reverse of usedSample property." .
<http://schema.org/identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing, such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links." .
